      "type": "uofa:Claim",
      "name": "CFD model credibly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for CPB device",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-primary-hemolysis-bench"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/result/synthesis-prior-hemolysis-studies",
      "type": "uofa:IntermediateResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior centrifugal pump hemolysis CFD studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior published hemolysis prediction studies using CFD for centrifugal blood pumps, including the Bludszuweit power-law model benchmarking (1995–2023), the FDA Critical Path Initiative pump dataset comparisons, and internal pre-submission validation exercises conducted across three independent laboratories. This synthesis established the baseline model-form confidence and informed the selection of hemolysis damage accumulation parameters used in the current COU. The aggregated evidence base spans more than 15 peer-reviewed publications and three independent experimental campaigns, providing strong a priori justification for the turbulence and hemolysis sub-model choices."
    },
    {
